text: Linda Hanley (born 8 June 1960) is an American beach volleyball player, born in Laguna Hills, California. She competed in the women's tournament at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta, with team mate Barbra Fontana. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1960 births Category:Living people Category:People from Laguna Hills, California Category:American women's beach volleyball players Category:Olympic beach volleyball players of the United States Category:Beach volleyball players at the 1996 Summer Olympics
